messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?

We heard a noise and looked in. The garage door was up. I thought the gentleman was backing out. I went back to my house, but he never backed out. I came back over, and his driver's side window is shattered, and he's injured and can't answer.
Okay, and the phone number you're calling from?
I'm calling from [caller provides phone number].
Okay, tell me exactly what happened.
He's inside. I don't know if somebody tried to shoot him, if he shot himself, or what. I don't know.
Was that at this location, correct?
Yes, send an ambulance in a hurry. An EMT. He's still alive. He's moving.
Okay. What's going on with him?
I don't know. The driver's side window is all bashed in, and he's got blood all over his head. He's not responding to me.
What's your name, sir?
My name is [caller provides name]. I think you need to hurry.
Yes, I'm sending help your way. I just want to ask you a few more questions, okay?
Go ahead, but send them while you're asking.
Yes, sir. They're already on the way. Are you with him now?
I'm standing right outside the garage door.
Can you tell me how old he is?
I don't know. He looks like maybe 35 or 40.
Okay, hang on one second for me, okay?
I apologize about that. How old is the patient again?
I'm not sure. He looks maybe 35 or 40.
Is he awake?
He's moving his head around, but he's not responding. I've called his name and asked what's going on, but he's not responding to that. His head's just kind of rolling around.
Is he conscious?
Well, I can't tell.
Is he breathing?
I can't tell that. I'm assuming he's breathing if he's moving his head around. Did not hear him talk or anything.
Okay. You said he's sitting in the car, right?
Correct. In the driver's seat.
Where exactly is he?
In the driver's seat, inside the garage.
Can you direct the emergency crews to him, sir?
Sure, sure.
Alright, I'm sending the paramedics to help you now. Just stay on the line. I'll tell you exactly what to do next.
Okay.
If it's safe to do so, see if he is conscious, breathing, or moving at all.
It's not safe for me to do. I don't want to put my hand in there.
Okay, well, help is on the way.
Alright, standing by. I've heard about break-ins in the area, and so I decided to walk over and take a look. The garage door was up, and I saw the window is shattered and he's got blood.
Just stand in line with me for now, okay, sir?
Okay, I'm here.
I got emergency crews on the way to you.
Very good. I'm standing at the street. If I see them coming down, I can direct them right in.
So he won't respond to you at all if you holler at him or anything?
Yeah, he didn't respond, but his head is kind of moving around.
Okay.
I've walked away from the car right now. I'm standing at the street.
The window shattered. The garage door was up, correct?
Yes.
Give me a second. I'll try to see where the emergency crews are, okay? Is he still moving around?
I don't know. I'm standing at the street now trying to wait for your vehicle.
Okay, where exactly are they coming from? Checking, got several people on the way.
Yes, please hurry. We're close to the hospital.
Well, it looks like one person is coming from Clay Road.
So you're saying his head is bloody?
Yes, the window is shattered. I don't know if he tried to shoot himself. I don't know what the situation is.
Is the driver's side window shattered, correct?
Yes, that's correct.
He's still moving around, so he's alive.
Okay, looks like I should have an officer coming up the roadway.
We need EMT.
Well, the officer's going to be there first. They're not going to come until we figure out what's going on, but EMT is on the way as well, okay?
They better hurry if this guy's got a shot at living.
Yes, sir. They're on the way as well, okay?
Okay, looks like the officer is coming up right now.
Is he there?
Yeah, he's just coming up right now.
Okay, I'm going to go ahead and let you go, sir, okay?
Okay, very good. Thank you.
